{"lemma":"ضَيْفِ","slug":"ضَيْفِ","root":"ض.#.ف","root_slug":"ض-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَيْف","root":"ضيف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26205","n26209","n26210"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%81%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guest(s)","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ إِنَّ هَٰؤُلَاءِ ضَيْفِي فَلَا تَفْضَحُونِ"},{"text":"هَلْ أَتَاكَ حَدِيثُ ضَيْفِ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الْمُكْرَمِينَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَافَ (ḍāfa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26205","headword_ar":"ضيّف","root":"Dyf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", intrans.: see 1, first and second sentences.       -A2-  As trans.: see 4, last sentence, in four places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day~afotuhu","text_ar":"ضَيَّفْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I protected him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defended him, from him who sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pursued, him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rendered him safe, secure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from fear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became at peace with him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used metaphorically. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n26209","headword_ar":"ضَيْفٌ","root":"Dyf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A guest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guests:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:) so called because adjoined to the family and fed with them: (Ham p. 124:) it is applied to one, and to a pl. number, (S, M, MA, O, Msb, K,) and to a male and to a female, (S, O, Msb, K,) because it is originally an inf. n.: (MA, Msb:) [as a sing.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDay~afN","text_ar":"مُضَيَّفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naziylN","text_ar":"نَزِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and applied to a pl. number, it may be pl. [or rather a quasi-pl. n.] of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^ifN","text_ar":"ضَايِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAzilN","text_ar":"نَازِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; thus being of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawozN","text_ar":"زَوْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomN","text_ar":"صَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and it is also pluralized, having for its pls."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoyaAfN","text_ar":"اَضْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyfaAnN","text_ar":"ضِيفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, MA, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuyuwfN","text_ar":"ضُيُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, MA, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaAfN","text_ar":"ضِيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, TA,) the first of which is properly a pl. of pauc., but is also used as a pl. of mult.: (M:) and a female is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DayofapN","text_ar":"ضَيْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DayofN","text_ar":"ضَيْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, O, Msb, K:) El-Ba'eeth says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laqFY Hamalatohu A^um~uhu wahoYa DayofapN"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A castaway with whom his mother became pregnant while she was a guest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, O:) or, accord. to AHeyth, the meaning here is that which follows. (O.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DayofapN","text_ar":"ضَيْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Menstruating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) so says AHeyth with reference to the citation above from El-Ba'eeth. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","S","M","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n26210","headword_ar":"ضِيفٌ","root":"Dyf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, O, K) of a valley (T, M) and of a mountain (M) [&c.: see 6]: and, as metaphorically used by an anonymous poet, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akar","text_ar":"ذَكَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaAyifu","text_ar":"مَضَايِفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fiY Diyfi fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فِى ضِيفِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in the vicinage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter, of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}